University of Alberta research found why knuckles really crack . 
 Study found  cracking is caused by rapid formation of gas-filled cavity . 
 Research also discovered a knuckle cracks in less than 310 milliseconds . 
 A study co-author was used as the guinea pig for the experiment . 
 Rapid magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) was used to capture 'the bones and fluids surrounding them, and critically, the formation of the air cavity'The researchers humorously dubbed their work the 'pull my finger study'